## Phase 1: Input Gathering

Collect required inputs via AskUserQuestion. Ask only for what is missing.

**Required:**
- Target PDB file path (or RCSB ID — will fetch)
- Target chain ID (default: A)
- Hotspot residues (e.g. "A47,A51,A89") — residues the binder must contact

**Optional (use defaults if not provided):**
- Binder length: default 65 residues (50–80 range; adjust based on target)
- Number of backbone designs: default 100
- Backend: auto-detect from config (prefer RFdiffusion3 if available, then BindCraft)
- Number of MPNN sequences per backbone: default 8
- Validation method: ESMFold (fast, screening) or AF2 multimer (accurate, final)
- Output directory: default `./binder_design_<target_name>_<timestamp>/`

**If RCSB ID provided** (4-char, e.g. "1YCR"):
```bash
TARGET_ID="<RCSB_ID>"
wget -q "https://files.rcsb.org/download/${TARGET_ID}.pdb" -O "${TARGET_ID}.pdb"
echo "Downloaded: ${TARGET_ID}.pdb"
```

**Summarize inputs before proceeding:**
```
TARGET: <path/id>
CHAIN: <chain>
HOTSPOTS: <residue list>
BINDER LENGTH: <n> residues
N DESIGNS: <n> backbones × <n> MPNN sequences
BACKEND: <backend>
VALIDATION: <ESMFold|AF2>
OUTPUT DIR: <path>
```

Confirm via AskUserQuestion before launching.

