## Phase 3: Backbone Generation

### Option A — RFdiffusion3

```bash
OUTPUT_DIR="<OUTPUT_DIR>"
mkdir -p "$OUTPUT_DIR/backbones"

python <RFDIFFUSION_PATH>/run_inference.py \
  inference.input_pdb=<TARGET_PDB> \
  inference.output_prefix="$OUTPUT_DIR/backbones/design" \
  inference.num_designs=<N_DESIGNS> \
  'contigmap.contigs=["<CHAIN>1-<TARGET_LEN>/0 <BINDER_LEN>-<BINDER_LEN>"]' \
  'ppi.hotspot_res=["<HOTSPOT_LIST>"]' \
  denoiser.noise_scale_ca=1 \
  denoiser.noise_scale_frame=1
```

Replace `<TARGET_LEN>` with the actual length of the target chain.
Replace `<HOTSPOT_LIST>` with space-separated hotspot strings like `["A47","A51","A89"]`.

### Option B — BindCraft

```bash
mkdir -p "<OUTPUT_DIR>"
cat > "<OUTPUT_DIR>/bindcraft_config.yaml" << YAML
target_pdb: <TARGET_PDB>
target_hotspot_res: "<HOTSPOT_CSV>"
binder_len: <BINDER_LEN>
num_designs: <N_DESIGNS>
filters:
  plddt: 75
  iptm: 0.55
  i_pae: 18
YAML

python <BINDCRAFT_PATH>/run_bindcraft.py \
  --config "<OUTPUT_DIR>/bindcraft_config.yaml" \
  --output "<OUTPUT_DIR>/bindcraft_output/"
```

BindCraft does backbone + MPNN + AF2 validation in one pass — skip Phases 4 and 5 for BindCraft, go directly to Phase 6.

