## Phase 4: Sequence Design (MPNN)

*Skip if using BindCraft — it handles this internally.*

```bash
BACKBONES_DIR="<OUTPUT_DIR>/backbones"
SEQS_DIR="<OUTPUT_DIR>/sequences"
mkdir -p "$SEQS_DIR"

# Build chain specification JSON
python3 - << 'PYEOF'
import json, glob, os
pdbs = glob.glob(f"{os.environ.get('BACKBONES_DIR', '<OUTPUT_DIR>/backbones')}/*.pdb")
chains_dict = {os.path.basename(p): ["<BINDER_CHAIN>"] for p in pdbs}
with open("<OUTPUT_DIR>/chains_to_design.json", "w") as f:
    json.dump(chains_dict, f)
print(f"Found {len(pdbs)} backbone PDBs")
PYEOF

python <MPNN_PATH>/protein_mpnn_run.py \
  --pdb_path "$BACKBONES_DIR" \
  --pdb_path_jsonl "" \
  --chain_id_jsonl "<OUTPUT_DIR>/chains_to_design.json" \
  --num_seq_per_target <N_MPNN_SEQS> \
  --sampling_temp 0.1 \
  --seed 37 \
  --batch_size 1 \
  --out_folder "$SEQS_DIR"
```

After MPNN:
```bash
# Count sequences generated
find "<OUTPUT_DIR>/sequences" -name "*.fa" | xargs grep -c "^>" 2>/dev/null | \
  awk -F: '{sum += $2} END {print "Total sequences designed:", sum}'
```

