## Phase 5: Structure Validation

*Skip if using BindCraft.*

Select validation method based on config and user preference:

### ESMFold (fast screening — use for first pass)

```bash
SEQS_DIR="<OUTPUT_DIR>/sequences"
VALIDATION_DIR="<OUTPUT_DIR>/validation_esmfold"
mkdir -p "$VALIDATION_DIR"

# Concatenate all sequences into one FASTA for batch folding
cat "$SEQS_DIR"/*.fa > "$VALIDATION_DIR/all_sequences.fasta"

python <ESMFOLD_PATH>/esm/scripts/fold.py \
  -i "$VALIDATION_DIR/all_sequences.fasta" \
  -o "$VALIDATION_DIR/" \
  --num-recycles 4 \
  --cpu-only  # remove if GPU available
```

### AF2 Multimer (accurate — use for top candidates)

Use AF2 multimer on the top 20 candidates by ESMFold pLDDT. Always run multimer
mode for interface validation — monomer mode cannot assess binding.

```bash
TOP_SEQS_DIR="<OUTPUT_DIR>/top_candidates_seqs"
mkdir -p "$TOP_SEQS_DIR"
# (populate with top 20 FASTA files from ESMFold ranking)

python <AF2_PATH>/run_alphafold.py \
  --fasta_paths="$TOP_SEQS_DIR/<candidate>.fasta" \
  --model_preset=multimer \
  --max_template_date=2020-01-01 \
  --output_dir="<OUTPUT_DIR>/validation_af2/" \
  --use_gpu_relax=True
```

